Manchester City boss Pep Guardiola speaking at a press conference, went on to make a long and passionate defence of his side after their latest stumble on the European stage. Manchester City lost a two-goal lead and were beaten in extra time by Real Madrid. City were heading for the Champions League final with just minutes to go in the Bernabeu. But Real Madrid reached the Champions League final in the most dramatic of circumstances, pulling one goal back in the 90th minute, equalising in stoppage time and winning it in extra time.